page.title: 09South east of Cambridge
page.content:
This square is dominated by a hill which gives a commanding view of the surrounding countryside.
Addenbrookes Hospital can be clearly seen, across a gently sloping field, a bit further down the hill, is a beautifull cottage. This square consists primarily of agricultural land, with the occasional house.
At Caius College Farm there were three main buildings. One was derelict, while the other two were still being lived in. It had one or two barns and a lot of machinary. There were also large areas of arable land. Radishes and oil seed rape were mainly grown.
